## ⌘ ÆTHEROS — The Hermetic Operating System
◯ The endgame — a hermetic desktop environment where AI is the substrate, not a chat window.
   Files, windows, and processes all flow through the oracle. As above (the OS), so below (the code).
   The planned Mac app (AetherCodex.app) is the prima materia — a stepping stone toward an OS where
   correspondence and mentalism are the UX, not just metaphors.
     ◯ Mac app: native AI editor replacing TextMate (Swift + AppKit)
     ◯ File system as alchemical vessel: every file operation is a ritual
     ◯ Hermetic window manager: windows correspond to planes of consciousness
     ◯ Process daemon: background conjurations, continuous divination
     ◯ Unified tool plane: CLI tools and OS share the same instrumenta

## ⌘ ÆTHERTERMINAL — The Divinatory Terminal
◯ The CLI's evolution into a terminal emulator where tool calls render inline with ANSI art,
   commands are divined as you type, and the shell-oracle boundary dissolves.
   The `TerminalStream` work (colored tool events in CLI) is the first cell dividing.
     ◯ Inline tool rendering: read_file results appear as syntax-highlighted panels
     ◯ Predictive command divination: shell completion via oracle
     ◯ ÆST (Hermetic Shell): a shell where `ls` consults Mnemosyne for file notes
     ◯ Terminal multiplexing: multiple oracle sessions in split panes
     ◯ Scrollback is memory: terminal history feeds into context window

